# vade-app/vade-agent-logs#64 — transcripts encryption recipient
#
# Public X25519 recipient for encrypting redacted session transcripts
# at-rest in Cloudflare R2. The matching private identity lives in
# 1Password at op://COO/transcripts-age-key/credential and is fetched
# into TRANSCRIPTS_AGE_IDENTITY by fetch_coo_secrets — read by the
# Stage-1 transcript-analyzer sub-agent (Batch 3) at decryption time.
#
# Pubkeys are safe to commit; the private identity is the only thing
# that protects the data. Loss of the 1Password slot makes every
# transcript ever encrypted with this recipient permanently unreadable.
#
# Rotation: generate a new keypair locally (`age-keygen`), paste the
# new public key below, stash the private in 1Password (keep the prior
# slot under op://COO/transcripts-age-key-archive until a re-encrypt
# sweep over historical R2 objects completes), update this file. The
# export hook reads this file at run time, so a single PR rotation
# takes effect on next session-end.
#
# Generated: 2026-04-28 (Batch 2 of issue #64).
